My last letter as a Member of Congress was sent to @POTUS tonight, urging him to award the Medal of Honor posthumously to Rhode Islander First Sergeant Peter Andrew McKenna. 

He is a true American hero who embodied the very best of our country and our shared American values.

Every day, over the last 12 years, I put my heart and soul into the work of improving the lives of every Rhode Islander. I’m so proud of all we accomplished.

Thank you, for the honor and the privilege, Rhode Island.

bit.ly/Cicilline12yrsOfServi…

This will be my last week serving in the U.S. House of Representatives. It has been the honor of my life to represent RI's First District in Congress. Thank you to everyone who placed their faith & trust in me over the last 12 years.

Some final thoughts⤵️
bit.ly/LookingBackOn12Years

With antisemitism on the rise, and reaching historic levels, we must come together to stand against this bigotry and hate. #NeverAgain
